race.comment: SO BE INSPIRED (5) drops back in class after a poor run at Murwillumbah 4 weeks ago, where maybe the loss of a shoe affected her that day. She looked much better at a recent Gold Coast trial, and the addition of a tongue tie could be the key. She cops a wide gate, but can still bounce back into form immediately. MISHANI STELLER (12) overcame a wide gate and a tough trip to score by nearly a length here 5 weeks ago. She is nicely weighted again with a 3kg claim, and from an even better gate, she can repeat the dose. FANCI FLEUR (6) went back to back on the picnic circuit, and her 2 starts since then have been a pair of solid third-place finishes. She cops a wide gate, but is still a must for all top 4 combos. MISTER TUDOR (7) changed stables and was produced to win fresh up off a long break at a recent Inverell picnic meeting a fortnight ago. He has obviously improved, and is an each-way threat again. MISS ZERMATT (4) has been disappointing since winning fresh up at Kilcoy. Go again.
